article.description: Mandell Thomas scored 26 points and Ryan Rhoomes added 20 more to propel Fordham to an 87-64 win over Manhattan on Saturday.
article.headline: Fordham cruises to 87-64 win over Manhattan
article.linkText: Fordham cruises to 87-64 win over Manhattan
article.story: NEW YORK -- Mandell Thomas scored 26 points and Ryan Rhoomes added 20 more to propel Fordham to an 87-64 win over Manhattan on Saturday. Thomas hit 9 of 18 from the field, including four 3-pointers, while Rhoomes made 9 of 11, grabbed 10 rebounds and blocked six shots. Christian Sengfelder contributed 16 points, Joseph Chartouny had 11 and Antwoine Anderson 10 for Fordham (4-1), which shot 56 percent from field and was 10 of 19 from 3-point range. Sengfelder's 3-pointer late in the first half sparked a 13-3 run stretching across both sides of the break to make it 46-33 with 18:35 left. The margin remained in double figures the rest of the way as the Rams continued to extend their advantage. Manhattan (1-3) got 24 points from Rich Williams and 13 from Tyler Wilson, who made 9 of 14 free throws.
